message.content: The slope between $(0,3)$ and $(-8,0)$ is $\frac{0-3}{-8-0}=-\frac{3}{8}$. So, the slope between $(0,3)$ and $(t,5)$ is also $-\frac38$. This gives us the equation $\frac{5-3}{t-0}=-\frac38\Rightarrow \frac{2}{t}=-\frac38$. Cross-multiplying yields $3\cdot2=-\frac38\cdot t\Rightarrow6=-\frac{3}{8}\cdot8\cdot t$. Simplifying the right side and dividing both sides by $6$ yields $t=\boxed{1}$.
